article.headline: Winthrop 64, Barton 51
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. -- Matt Morgan scored 14 points and Andy Buechert had 10 points and 18 rebounds as Winthrop pulled away late to defeat Barton College 64-51 on Saturday night. The Bulldogs (5-2), NCAA Division II champions in 2007, trailed Winthrop 41-39 with 10:23 remaining but scored just one point over the next 6:51 to fall behind 52-40 against the Eagles (4-4) with 3:53 to play. Barton missed eight shots from the field and turned the ball over four times during its run of futility before Klevin Pollard hit a jumper at the 3:32 mark. Winthrop also had an 11-1 run in the first half, after Barton had taken an 11-6 lead in the game's first 3:07. The Bulldogs missed 11 shots during that stretch and finished the game shooting 25.4 percent (16-for-63). Gerald Boston, the only Barton player to make at least half his shots (5-for-9), led the Bulldogs with 14 points.
